    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the Greek style of sculpture produced by Lysippos during the 4th century BCE and characterized by figures that convey a greater sense of height through slender bodies and small heads, and a sense of three-dimensional movement that departs from earlier more static frontal poses.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Alude a un estilo de escultura griega producido por Lysippos durante el siglo IV a.C y caracterizado por figuras que transmiten un mayor sentido de altura a través de cuerpos esbeltos y cabezas pequeñas y un sentido de movimiento tridimensional que se aleja de las antiguas poses frontales más estáticas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de Griekse stijl in de beeldhouwkunst die werd vervaardigd door Lysippos tijdens de vierde eeuw v. Chr. De stijl kenmerkt zich door beelden die langer lijken door de slanke lichamen en de kleine hoofden, en door een idee van driedimensionale beweeglijkheid die afwijkt van de vroegere, meer statische beelden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052398/Encyclopedie van de kunst (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱於西紀元前四世紀間，由利斯皮斯（Lysippos）所創作出的希臘雕塑風格，其特徵為透過較為纖細的身體與小型的頭部，表達出更為高佻的感覺，以及一種脫離了早期較為靜態之身體正面姿勢的三度空間動作感。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
